    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/26071</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Mexican Affairs, Department of
                        State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: By your direction, I delivered the
                    following message to Mr. Tellez<note n="26" xml:id="d577fn26">First Secretary of
                        Mexican Embassy.</note> on June 22: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“It has been intimated to the Department that Mr. de la Huerta<note
                                n="27" xml:id="d577fn27">Mexican Secretary of Hacienda.</note> is
                            considering coming to Washington to call on the President and the
                            Secretary of State, if his visit would not be unwelcome. You <pb
                                facs="0784" n="670" xml:id="pg_670"/> may assure Mr. de la Huerta
                            that, should he come to Washington, the President and the Secretary of
                            State, naturally in a personal and unofficial capacity, would be pleased
                            to have a talk with him.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">atthew</hi>] E. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >anna</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
